	<h2> Screening Experience: </h2>
	<p> As the lights dimmed and the opening credits of <i>One Piece</i> rolled on the big screen, a wave of anticipation swept through the audience. The three episodes were stitched together with the recaps and endings skipped, forming one cohesive storyline which snugly fit within the runtime of one hour. The screening delivered on its promises, showcasing intense battles, emotional moments, and unexpected plot twists. Gasps, cheers, and laughter echoed through the auditorium as the audience was fully immersed in the world of pirates, adventure, and camaraderie. The screening experience was a rollercoaster of emotions, taking the audience on an unforgettable journey through the world of <i>One Piece</i>. Gasps filled the room during the shocking turn of events in episode 1070, as the unexpected death of Luffy left hearts heavy and eyes glistening with emotion. However, the atmosphere shifted in episode 1071, when the much-anticipated<i> Gear 5</i> was finally unveiled in a jaw-dropping sequence, igniting cheers of awe and admiration from the captivated audience. The intensity escalated further in episode 1072, as the electrifying showdown between Luffy and the formidable Kaido unfolded, leaving viewers on the edge of their seats with adrenaline coursing through their veins. The screening seamlessly blended heart-wrenching moments, thrilling revelations, and pulse-pounding action, creating an immersive experience that left a lasting impression on every attendee.
	</p>
